SVSS test

Running SVSS test to see which variables are included

Logistic model comparing original Dissertation model with SVSS predictors

##Correlation Matrices on select vars Note that in preparation for modeling, we examine all of the variables recommended in the SVSS test, plus variables that were significant in the Chi-Square and Anova tests, and are relevant to the literature based on domain knowledge.

Given the high correlation between MHV and MHI, we drop MHI.

Note that there is significant correlation between several variables of interest, including MPR, MHV, tax base, fWhite, and population density.

Some notes: -MPR ideology is negatively correlated with MHV: as MHV increase, republican ideology decreases (suggests lower-income is correlated with republicanism) -MPR ideology is positively correlated with tax base -Tax base and MHV are positively correlated -FWhite and MPR ideology are positively correlated -fWhite is negatively correlated with a lot of the exposure variables, like Hurricane, ZCTA_Shore, and count_FEMA SFHA. However, need these controls. - Given

Going to have to select specific hypotheses to test one at a time.
